" {\n    \"title\": \"'Find the middle index of an array (Easy)',\n    \"description\": 'Given an array of integers, return the index of its middle value. If the length of the array is even, return the larger of the two middle indices.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef find_middle(arr: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `arr` (list[int]): A sorted and non-empty array of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the index of the middle value in the given array, or the larger indices if the length of the array is even.\\n',\n    \"code\": \"def find_middle(arr: list[int]) -> int:\\n    # Check if the array has an odd number of elements\\n    odd = len(arr) % 2 == 1\\n    \\n    # Calculate the middle index based on whether the length is even or odd\\n    mid_index = len(arr) // 2\\n    \\n    # If the array has an odd number of elements, return the single middle index\\n    if odd:\\n        return mid_index\\n    \\n    # Otherwise, return the larger of the two middle indices\\n    else:\\n        return mid_index - 1, mid_index\\n\",\n    \"tests\": ['assert find_middle([1, 2, 3, 4]) == 2', 'assert find_middle([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == 3', 'assert find_middle([0, 1, 2]) == 1', 'assert find_middle([0, 1, 2, 2, 3]) == (1, 2)']\n   }"